talog. I'm interested in graduate school. Who should I call? Dr. Lisa Kennon is our Graduate Coordinator. You can set up a meeting with Dr. Kennon by calling or emailing her directly: 940.565.4257 | kennon@unt.edu Currently all of our other academic advisors work with undergraduate students. I just have a quick question for an advisor; do I need to make an appointment? If you have a general question about academics, scheduling, equivalencies, or need to be connected with campus resources, you can email your advisor. For more specific questions, your advisor may ask that you schedule an appointment to have your concern adequately addressed. What are my degree requirements? BS in Digital Retailing (DRTL) BS in Home Furnishings Merchandising (HFMD) BS in Hospitality Management (HMGT) BS in Merchandising (MDSE) BS in Retailing (RETL)   These degree requirement sheets reflect the most current catalog year. Please see your advisor to obtain a degree requirement sheet for your specific catalog year. Schedule of Classes Registration Calendars Excessive Hours Information Repeated Courses Information Six-Rule Drop Policy Information Graduation Information Financial Aid- Student Academic Progress (SAP) Contact Us: College of Merchandising, Hospitality & Tourism 1155 Union Circle, #311100 Denton, TX 76203-5017 USA Voice: 940-565-2436 Fax: 940.565.4348 Visit Us: Chilton Hall Room Number: 331, 410 S. Avenue C Denton, TX 76201 http://cmht.unt.edu/ Email us: Have questions on content? Please contact us. cmht@unt.edu Technical problems: Have questions concerning how the site runs? Sampath.Pamidimukkala@unt.edu UNT System: UNT Home UNT System UNT Dallas UNT Health Science Center Site last updated on May 1, 2017 Disclaimer | AA/EOE/ADA | Privacy Statement | Web Accessibility Policy | State of Texas Online | Emergency Preparedness 